  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10068099/getting-random-value-from-a-sqlite-table",
  "title" : "Getting random value from a SQLite table",
  "body" : "<p>I am currently working on an Android app and I am trying to get a random value from a database table that looks like this:</p>\n<div class=\"s-table-container\"><table class=\"s-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>ID</th>\n<th>Score</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>20</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14</td>\n<td>15</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>(lets assume these are the only values in the table)</p>\n<p>I would like to get a random value from this table that has ID 1 40% of the time, ID 2 10% of the time, ID 5 10% of the time and so on...<br />\nIf that is even possible, how would you go about it?</p>\n"
}